article.headline: East Carolina 93, VCU 90
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- Darrius Morrow hit a free throw to give East Carolina the deciding lead in overtime, and Brock Young hit two more with 10 seconds remaining to help seal the Pirates' 93-90 win against Virginia Commonwealth on Tuesday night. The Pirates (4-1) outscored the Rams (2-2) 11-8 in overtime. James Legan led the Pirates with 20 points, Sam Hinnant added 18 and Young chipped in 17 and dished-out 11 assists. Eric Maynor led the Rams with a game-high 35 points, and Larry Sanders added 16 points and 14 rebounds. East Carolina, who came back from a 37-33 halftime deficit, shot 50.7 percent (34 of 67) from the field compared to a 41.6 mark (32 of 77) for the Rams.
